l), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705188,"age":7,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":42,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Burnell was born about 1217, in Garboldisham, Norfolk, England, his father, Sir Hugh Burnell, was 23 and his mother, Petronell Cheyney, was 30. He had at least 1 daughter. He died after 1274, in Oxborough, Norfolk, England."},"et":{"about 1217–after 1274":"umbes 1217–pärast 1274","1217–1274":"1217–1274","1234–Female":"1234–Surnud","1195–1242":"1195–1242","1188–Female":"1188–Surnud","1217":"1217","1259":"1259","about 1217":"umbes 1217","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1188":"1188","1242":"1242","1274":"1274","after 1274":"pärast 1274","1195":"1195","Oxborough, Norfolk, England":"Oxborough, Norfolk, England","Garboldisham, Norfolk, England":"Garboldisham, Norfolk, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"about 1217–after 1274":"noin 1217–1274 jälkeen","1217–1274":"1217–1274","1234–Female":"1234–Kuollut","1195–1242":"1195–1242","1188–Female":"1188–Kuollut","1217":"1217","1259":"1259","about 1217":"noin 1217","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1188":"1188","1242":"12